BEGIN NOW The moonlight fades from flower and tree, END
BEGIN NOW And the stars dim one by one; END
BEGIN NOW The tale is told, the song is sung, END
BEGIN NOW And the Fairy feast is done. END
BEGIN NOW The night-wind rocks the sleeping flowers, END
BEGIN NOW And sings to them, soft and low. END
BEGIN NOW The early birds erelong will wake: END
BEGIN NOW 'T is time for the Elves to go. END
BEGIN NOW O'er the sleeping earth we silently pass, END
BEGIN NOW Unseen by mortal eye, END
BEGIN NOW And send sweet dreams, as we lightly float END
BEGIN NOW Through the quiet moonlit sky;-- END
BEGIN NOW For the stars' soft eyes alone may see, END
BEGIN NOW And the flowers alone may know, END
BEGIN NOW The feasts we hold, the tales we tell: END
BEGIN NOW So 't is time for the Elves to go. END
BEGIN NOW From bird, and blossom, and bee, END
BEGIN NOW We learn the lessons they teach; END
BEGIN NOW And seek, by kindly deeds, to win END
BEGIN NOW A loving friend in each. END
BEGIN NOW And though unseen on earth we dwell, END
BEGIN NOW Sweet voices whisper low, END
BEGIN NOW And gentle hearts most joyously greet END
BEGIN NOW The Elves where'er they go. END
BEGIN NOW When next we meet in the Fairy dell, END
BEGIN NOW May the silver moon's soft light END
BEGIN NOW Shine then on faces gay as now, END
BEGIN NOW And Elfin hearts as light. END
BEGIN NOW Now spread each wing, for the eastern sky END
BEGIN NOW With sunlight soon will glow. END
BEGIN NOW The morning star shall light us home: END
BEGIN NOW Farewell! for the Elves must go. END
BEGIN NOW As the music ceased, with a soft, rustling sound the Elves END
BEGIN NOW The lonely sunsets flare forlorn END
BEGIN NOW Down valleys dreadly desolate; END
BEGIN NOW The lordly mountains soar in scorn END
BEGIN NOW As still as death, as stern as fate. END
BEGIN NOW _The lonely sunsets flame and die; END
BEGIN NOW The giant valleys gulp the night; END
BEGIN NOW The monster mountains scrape the sky, END
BEGIN NOW Where eager stars are diamond-bright._ END
BEGIN NOW So gaunt against the gibbous moon, END
BEGIN NOW Piercing the silence velvet-piled, END
BEGIN NOW A lone wolf howls his ancient rune -- END
BEGIN NOW The fell arch-spirit of the Wild. END
BEGIN NOW _O outcast land! O leper land! END
BEGIN NOW Let the lone wolf-cry all express END
BEGIN NOW The hate insensate of thy hand, END
BEGIN NOW Thy heart's abysmal loneliness._ END
